      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 4 article on death of patient in gene therapy experiment at St Elizabeth's Medical Center, Boston; hospital failed to report death to its institutional review board, not Food and Drug Administration</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Thursday about the death of a patient in a gene therapy experiment at St. Elizabeth's Medical Center in Boston misidentified the authority to which the hospital failed to report the death. It is the institutional review board of St. Elizabeth's, not the Food and Drug Administration.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article on Thursday about the death of a patient in a gene therapy experiment at St. Elizabeth's Medical Center in Boston misidentified the authority to which the hospital failed to report the death. It is the institutional review board of St. Elizabeth's, not the Food and Drug Administration.</p>
      </block>
